Package: explain-tool
Architecture: all
Depends: python3 (>= 3.10), ${misc:Depends}
Recommends: python3-rich
Description: Linux command explanation tool with triple perspectives
 A command-line tool for Linux that explains the meaning and usage of
 shell commands from three angles:
 .
  - Quick mode: one-line summary for fast lookup
  - General perspective: sysadmin / DevOps best practices
  - Security perspective: pentesting / CTF / privilege escalation
 .
 Supports OpenAI, DeepSeek, and local Ollama backends.
 Bilingual output: Chinese (zh) and English (en).
 Compatible with Debian/Ubuntu/Kali, Fedora/RHEL, Arch, openSUSE, Alpine.
